==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Etymon
<hw>Et"y*mon</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it> E.
<plw>Etymons</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>, Gr. <plw>Etyma</plw>
<pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[L., fr. Gr. <grk>'e`tymon</grk> the true
literal sense of a word according to its derivation, an etymon, fr. <?/
true, real, prob, akin to Skr. <ets>sotya</ets>, E. <ets>sooth</ets>.
See <er>Sooth</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>An original form; primitive
word; root.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Original or fundamental signification.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Given as the <qex>etymon</qex> or genuine sense of the word.</q>
<rj><qau>Coleridge.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Etypical</ent>⟦br⟧
